subSubSection.paragraph:
In order to verify the characteristics of 

C. montana

we obtained photos of the 
holotype
stored in the British Museum of Natural History (
Fig. 23
) through kind help from Dr. Ben Price. We could ascertain that (
Fig. 23b
): 1) S9–10 are indeed dorsally completely pale, with only the lower sides black; 2) the color is a mix of paler blue and ochre, although ochre is the overriding impression; 3) the superior appendages have an almost square ventral expansion well proximal of the apex of the appendages, (
Fig. 23a
); 4) the sides of the thorax are clearly blue with a thin black line over the metapleural suture, (
Fig. 23a, c
); 5) the mesepisternum has a long antehumeral stripe that in dorsal view appears somewhat curved; 6) the middle pronotal lobe of the prothorax has large yellow areas laterally and the propleuron is largely yellowish, the anterior and posterior pronotal lobes connected by black over the middle of the middle pronotal lobe only.
